  "prompt": "What are the best job sites for mid-level and senior roles?",
  "response": "Here are some of the best job sites for mid-level and senior professional roles:\n\n1. LinkedIn Jobs\n- Extensive professional network\n- High-quality job listings\n- Great for networking and professional connections\n\n2. Indeed\n- Large job aggregator\n- Wide range of industries and levels\n- Easy to search and apply\n\n3. Glassdoor\n- Job listings with company reviews\n- Salary information\n- Insights into company culture\n\n4. ZipRecruiter\n- AI-powered job matching\n- Good for professionals across industries\n- Sends applications directly to employers\n\n5. Monster\n- Long-standing job search platform\n- Strong for mid to senior-level roles\n- Multiple filtering options\n\n6. Robert Half\n- Specialized in professional and technical roles\n- Strong for finance, accounting, and technology\n- Recruitment and job placement services\n\n7. AngelList (for tech/startup roles)\n- Startup-focused job board\n- Tech and innovation positions\n- Equity and compensation details\n\n8. Dice (for tech professionals)\n- Specialized technology job site\n- High-quality tech and IT roles\n- Targeted for experienced professionals\n\n9. Executive recruiters like Korn Ferry\n- Specialized in senior executive placements\n- High-level networking opportunities\n- Personalized job matching\n\nEach platform has unique strengths, so using multiple sites can maximize job search effectiveness.",
